The National Identity Management Commission (NIMC), said that the mobile app that will allow Nigerians access to personal National Identification Number (NIN) and registration have not been approved for public use. The Head of Corporate Communications, NIMC, Kayode Adegoke, who disclosed this in statement issued yesterday in Abuja, said the commission has receives several complaints about the NIMC mobile app. The commission statement is coming after Some Nigerians who has tried to use the NIMC mobile app had complained about the flaws, including wrong identities. Adegoke said, “We will like Nigerians to be aware that the App is a novel innovation by the Commission, but it is yet to be officially approved for public consumption. “The App is still in the test environment and currently being fine-tuned to give users the best experience with adequate privacy and data security safeguards.  